{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17619638","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17619638"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:33:59+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:33:59+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16569"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16569","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16569"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.13,0.21,0.13,0,0.54]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9260"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75569"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9260","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9260"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16569"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61086"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"32"},{"type":"tags","id":"35"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"212"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5862"},{"type":"tags","id":"5931"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21938"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21940"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75569","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75569"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EVestibular migraine is a common cause of recurrent vertigo, affecting approximately 1% of the general population. It frequently co-exists with other types of migraine headaches.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the diagnostic biomarker for vestibular migraine?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Elevated serum calcitonin gene-related peptide","Increased serum substance P levels","Abnormal cerebrospinal fluid prostaglandin levels","Elevated serum serotonin levels","No specific biological marker exists"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is that \u003Cstrong\u003Eno specific biological marker exists\u003C/strong\u003E for vestibular migraine. The diagnosis is based on clinical criteria including:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHistory of repeated episodes of vestibular symptoms \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHistory of migraines \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETemporal association between vestibular symptoms and migraine features\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlternative diagnosis does not provide better explanation \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EElevated serum calcitonin gene-related peptide\u003C/strong\u003E - While this may be elevated during migraine attacks, it is not specific or diagnostic for vestibular migraine\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased serum substance P levels\u003C/strong\u003E - While substance P is involved in pain pathways, it is not a diagnostic marker for vestibular migraine\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAbnormal cerebrospinal fluid prostaglandin levels\u003C/strong\u003E - While prostaglandins may play a role in migraine pathophysiology, this is not a validated diagnostic marker\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EElevated serum serotonin levels\u003C/strong\u003E - While serotonin is involved in migraine pathophysiology, serum levels are not diagnostic\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDiagnostic workup may include tests to rule out other causes of vertigo, but these tests are typically normal in vestibular migraine.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Vestibular migraine is diagnosed based on clinical criteria as there are no specific biological markers or diagnostic tests.","The diagnosis of vestibular migraine requires a history of migraine headaches and recurrent vestibular symptoms.","Laboratory tests and imaging studies in vestibular migraine are typically normal and are mainly used to exclude other conditions."],"references":["Martin VT, Feoktistov A, Solomon GD. A rational approach to migraine diagnosis and management in primary care. Ann Med. 2021 Dec;53(1):1979-1990. doi: 10.1080/07853890.2021.1995626. PMID: 34714201; PMCID: PMC8567924.","Yan BM, Gibson Depoy EM, Ahmad A, Nahas SJ. Biomarkers in Migraine. Neurol India. 2021 Mar-Apr;69(Supplement):S17-S24. doi: 10.4103/0028-3886.315988. PMID: 34003145.","Weatherall MW. The diagnosis and treatment of chronic migraine. Ther Adv Chronic Dis. 2015 May;6(3):115-23. doi: 10.1177/2040622315579627. PMID: 25954496; PMCID: PMC4416971."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61086"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16569"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61086","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61086"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-30T11:28:25+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-30T11:29:31+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9260"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75569"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"7","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/7"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Neurology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationsh